settings.title: ETHICALLY MADE YOGAWEAR, SWIMWEAR, LINEN AND MORE
settings.text:
•••

First imagined in the sand on the Australian coastal town of Torquay

Inspired by thoughtful Scandinavian/Nordic simplicity

Given life and flavoured on the magical island of Bali, Indonesia

•••

We are a small, family run brand ensuring quality, transparency, eco-consciousness and sustainable manufacturing practices.

We are dedicated to thoughtful slow creation. Reducing unnecessary impact on other beings and our planet while providing an alternative to mass production and fast fashion.

Our garments are made in beautiful simple shapes, earthy colours and plant dyes from recycled or organic materials. Collections are purposely created in small, sustainable runs and we plan to run out of stock. Everything is cut, sewn and dyed by loving human hand, and we ensure that every person involved in production works in comfortable, safe conditions.

•••

The name Indigo Luna came to us when we first began experimenting with natural dyes. We fell completely in love with the beauty and complexity of the Indigo plant and the way we could create earthy colours from nature that doesn't have a negative impact on our planet. This has been a continuing thread throughout our journey, and every decision we make is chosen to benefit the environment and health of the workers over profits.

We want you to feel the love in each hand made stitch and understand that there are real loving humans creating these garments. This is NOT fast fashion.

Creations designed to celebrate the female form, by providing simple, minimalistic shapes in eco-conscious fabrics. Designed for all bodies no matter your moon cycle or if you are creating life. We believe in female empowerment, with two of three directors being female as well as 93% of all employed staff.

We are really excited about improving and continuing our path towards sustainability. We recoginse that there is so much to learn and many new ways to adapt and evolve for the better. We celebrate just how far we have come as a small brand and realise how far we have to go. We want you to come on this journey with us and have honest and real conversations to create a new fashion industry we want to be a part of. Thank you for being a part of our story.

settings.title: OUR STORY
settings.richtext:
We are a small, family run brand ensuring quality, transparency, eco-consciousness and sustainable manufacturing practices.

The name Indigo Luna came to us when we first began experimenting with natural dyes. We fell completely in love with the beauty and complexity of the Indigo plant and the way we could create earthy colours from nature that doesn't have a negative impact on our planet.

This has been a continuing thread throughout our journey, and every decision we make is chosen to benefit the environment and health of the workers over profits. The importance of creating while also leaving behind the smallest footprint we can. Choose well, buy less, make it last. 

To us, the use of plant dyes encapsulates the slow, carefully chosen values of Indigo Luna and also the changing narrative that conscious consumers, like you, are driving. Ultimately our own choices will drive change. By supporting ethical brands you are directly helping to create the world you want to see around you. 

We want you to feel the love in each hand made stitch and understand that there are real loving humans creating these garments. This is NOT fast fashion.

settings.title: DESIGN
settings.richtext: Our Bali-based team spends months creating minimalist designs that sit beautifully on all kinds of bodies and through a woman's life's different cycles and seasons.

settings.title: FABRICS
settings.richtext: We source always the most sustainable and high-quality materials available, to bring our designs to life. Like GOTS Certified Organic Cotton, Plant Viscose, Modal or Recycled ECONYL®.

settings.title: PLANT DYES
settings.richtext: Our signature plant-dyed technique allows us to create earthy colours from nature that don't have a negative impact on our planet. All waste produced is 100% organic and compostable.

settings.title: PRODUCTION
settings.richtext: We work hand to hand with our women-run production team, to ensure that all the garments are handmade with positive intention in Bali, in comfortable, safe, and fair working conditions.

settings.title: PACKAGING & SHIPPING
settings.richtext: Our mailing bags are made from Cassava, and they are 100% compostable. We also offset our carbon emissions by paying extra for each shipment.

settings.text:
The small leaf in our logo represents the choices that we want to always make. The importance of creating while also leaving behind the smallest footprint we can.

settings.text_2:
Our Modal Intimates are dyed using 100% plant dyes, creating natural colours directly from nature with all run-off and waste being organic or compostable.

Our Ananda Yoga Range is made from GOTS Certified Organic Cotton, ensuring strict social and environmental standards are met in production.

All of our Nylon Leggings and Swimwear created from Italian Recycled ECONYL®, material harvested from discarded fishing nets or REPREVE® recycled nylon from plastic bottles.

settings.title: Repreve®
settings.text: Our Maya range is made from 100% recycled plastic bottles, our use of REPREVE® gives new life to plastic waste that would otherwise end up in landfills or the ocean, emits reduced greenhouse gases and conserves energy and water in the process.

settings.title: ECONYL®
settings.text: Our swimwear styles are made from ECONYL®, a 100% regenerated nylon fibre made from post-consumer nylon waste such as carpets and fishing nets. Regular nylon is made from non-renewable petroleum oil which is a significant contributor to global warming. By using regenerated nylon instead of new nylon, we are diverting goods from landfill and giving them a new life. This process reduces the global warming impact of nylon by up to 90% compared with material made from oil.

settings.title: Organic Cotton
settings.text: We use Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS) certified organic cotton. This fabric is soft, durable, natural and biodegradable. Grown without the use of pesticides or synthetic fertilisers, organic cotton uses significantly less water, relying predominantly on rainwater. Organic cotton reduces environmental footprint and promotes safe work and better livelihoods for farmers and their families. GOTS certified organic cotton is considered the leading global standard on sustainable processing for the textile industry.
